# Sequence 03 — CISO's audit export (PRD §6.3)

The "audit" journey. The customer CISO opens the audit view in the Forge console, filters by tenant + date range + actor, and exports a SOC 2-friendly artefact. The platform's job is to make the query fast, the data complete, and the export redaction-safe.

## Diagram

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor CISO as Customer CISO
    participant Console as Forge Console (Next.js)
    participant Orch as Master Orchestrator
    participant ReadAPI as Audit Read API (Postgres replica in audit account)
    participant AuditDB as Audit account Postgres
    participant S3 as Audit account S3 (object_store)
    participant Bus as NATS + event-bus-bridge
    participant AuditBus as Audit SQS

    CISO->>Console: open Audit view (tenant=acme-corp)
    Console->>Orch: GET /v1/tenants/acme-corp/audit/runs?date_range=2026-06-01..2026-06-17&actor=agent
    Orch->>Orch: validate JWT (aud=forge-runtime, tenant_id=acme-corp, role=ciso)
    Orch->>ReadAPI: forward query (read-only, replica-bound)
    ReadAPI->>AuditDB: SELECT tenant_id, event_id, ts, run_id, stage, actor, tool, result FROM audit_log WHERE tenant_id=acme-corp AND ts BETWEEN ... AND actor LIKE 'agent:%' ORDER BY ts DESC LIMIT 500
    AuditDB-->>ReadAPI: 500 rows
    ReadAPI-->>Orch: rows
    Orch-->>Console: JSON { runs: [...], next_page_token }

    CISO->>Console: filter tool=github.create_pull_request, click "Export"
    Console->>Orch: POST /v1/tenants/acme-corp/audit/exports {filters, format=csv}
    Orch->>Orch: idempotency_key=export-01J7Z...
    Orch->>ReadAPI: stream rows to S3 (signed URL, KMS-encrypted, expiry=1h)
    ReadAPI->>S3: PUT s3://fora-audit-acct/exports/acme-corp/2026-06-17/<export_id>.csv.gpg
    ReadAPI-->>Orch: export_id, size_bytes, row_count
    Orch-->>Console: {export_id, status=ready, signed_url}

    CISO->>Console: download .csv.gpg
    Console->>S3: GET (signed URL)
    S3-->>Console: gpg-encrypted CSV
    Note over CISO,S3: Customer decrypts with the GPG key delivered out-of-band at onboarding. The platform never sees the customer's private key.

    Note over Bus,AuditBus: Every event the CISO sees was shipped by the bridge from the runtime account. The runtime account has no IAM grant to read the audit account; a runtime compromise cannot rewrite history.
```

## Notes

- **Read replica in the audit account.** The CISO's query never hits the runtime account's primary. The replica is a streaming replica of the runtime's `audit_log` table (read-only, BYPASSRLS for the replica's `audit_reader` role only).
- **Redaction is at-write.** The runtime redacts PII + secrets on write (security memory §7.1). The CISO sees redacted rows by default; a "view redaction reason" action is audited and joinable.
- **GPG encryption on export.** The export is encrypted with the customer's GPG public key (delivered at onboarding, never stored in the platform). The platform can write the export; only the customer can read it.
- **Idempotency** on `POST /exports` — a network blip on the "Export" click is a no-op (ADR-0004). The export id is stable.
- **Audit export of the audit export.** Every read of the audit view is itself an audit row (`audit.audit_viewed`, `actor=ciso@acme-corp`, `filters=...`). The CISO can ask "who looked at this?" with one query.
- **SOC 2 control mapping** in `docs/runbooks/soc2-audit-export.md` (forthcoming) — the export is the artefact the auditor signs off on.
